cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with beamforming in wireless relay networks, which involves information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves power control and optimization, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes distributive strategies, which involves machine learning and optimization, and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category.
